# üì• SPLICE Plugin Testing Instructions for Danny

## üöÄ Quick Download Link

### Debug Version (v6.0.3-dev) - **Use This Version**
```
https://spliceclips.com/downloads/splice-v6.0.3-dev.zip
```

---

## üîß Step-by-Step Installation (READ CAREFULLY!)

### Step 1: Download the ZIP file
- Click the link above or paste it in your browser
- You'll download a file called `splice-v6.0.3-dev.zip`

### Step 2: UNZIP/EXTRACT the file ‚ö†Ô∏è IMPORTANT
- **On Mac**: Double-click the `.zip` file to extract it
- **On Windows**: Right-click ‚Üí "Extract All..."
- **AFTER extracting, you'll see**: `splice-v6.0.3.zxp` (THIS is what you need!)

### Step 3: Get ZXPInstaller (if you don't have it)
- Download from: https://aescripts.com/learn/zxp-installer/
- Install ZXPInstaller on your computer

### Step 4: Install the SPLICE plugin
- Open ZXPInstaller
- Drag the **`splice-v6.0.3.zxp`** file (from Step 2) into ZXPInstaller
- Wait for "Installation successful" message

### Step 5: Restart Premiere Pro completely
- Quit Premiere Pro fully (Cmd+Q on Mac, Alt+F4 on Windows)
- Reopen Premiere Pro

### Step 6: Open SPLICE panel
- Go to `Window ‚Üí Extensions ‚Üí SPLICE`

---

## ‚ö†Ô∏è COMMON MISTAKE

**Problem:** "I don't see a .zxp file!"

**Solution:** You need to **UNZIP** the downloaded file first!
- The download is a `.zip` file (archive)
- The `.zxp` file is **INSIDE** the zip
- Double-click the zip to extract it, then you'll see the `.zxp`

